<div class='communityQuestionSubTitle'>
Popular Answered Questions
</div>
<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1412991-i-was-drawn-to-the-book-by-seeing-karl">I was drawn to the book by seeing Karl Marlantes on The Vietnam War by Ken Burns. In the series, he said his motivation for enlisting was driven by a sense of guilt for letting others fight in his place (he was studying at Oxford at the time). 

I have to ask - Why was this book written as historical fiction? It seems like Marlantes&#39; real story was more intriguing than what he presented in the book. Just my $0.02!</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1412991'><a id="like_count_community_question_1412991" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1412991?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F6411016-matterhorn">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1412991-i-was-drawn-to-the-book-by-seeing-karl">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1412991-i-was-drawn-to-the-book-by-seeing-karl">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/31625134-jennifer"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1522438277i/31625134._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/31625134-jennifer">Jennifer</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Perhaps Marlantes did not want to &quot;out&quot; the people who were burdened with making so many bad decisions and putting so many soldiers in harm&apos;s way. Usi<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Perhaps Marlantes did not want to "out" the people who were burdened with making so many bad decisions and putting so many soldiers in harm's way. Using the cover of fiction, Marlantes could tell a story that was close to the horrible truth without hurting the people (and their families) who were running the show.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
